---
import Base from '@/layouts/Base.astro';
import PageHeader from '@/components/PageHeader.astro';
import { site } from '@/lib/site';
---

<Base
  title="About"
  description="About the Fair Food Pricing campaign — who I am, why I am doing this, and how to get in touch."
>
  <PageHeader
    eyebrow="Who and why"
    title="About this campaign"
    intro="A short, honest explainer. No mission statement, no founder photo."
  />

  <div class="container-wide py-6 md:py-8">
    <article class="prose prose-neutral [&_a]:text-primary max-w-4xl">
      <h2>Who am I</h2>
      <p>
        I am <strong>{site.publisher.name}</strong> — a UK voter, not an organisation, not a charity,
        not a CIC. There is no team, no payroll, no funding from any retailer, retail body, technology
        vendor, or political party. There is no donation page because there is nothing to donate to.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you want to reach me, the address is
        <a href={`mailto:${site.publisher.email}`}>{site.publisher.email}</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Why I built this</h2>
      <p>
        Most political problems are reactive. We notice a harm, then legislate after the fact. This
        one is different. The harm is on the horizon, the hardware is being installed across UK
        supermarkets right now, and the practices it makes possible — personalised pricing of
        essential food — have not yet become normal. The window to draw the line in advance is open.
        It will not be open for long.
      </p>

      <h2>What you can do</h2>
      <ol>
        <li><a href="/find-your-mp">Write to your MP</a>. This is the single biggest lever.</li>
        <li>
          Forward the <a href="/downloads">one-page summary</a> to any MP, peer, councillor or journalist
          you know.
        </li>
        <li>
          Share <a href="/the-evidence">the evidence page</a> with anyone who thinks this is overblown.
        </li>
      </ol>

      <h2>Endorsements</h2>
      <p>
        None yet. The site launched on <time datetime="2026-05-17">17 May 2026</time>. If you are an
        MP, a charity, a faith group, an academic or a trade body and you would consider endorsing
        the proposal, please get in touch.
      </p>
    </article>
  </div>
</Base>
